Ahead of the 2023 general election, the Peoples Democratic PartyÂ (PDP), has reportedly postponed its presidential primaries. It was gathered that the primaries for aspirants contesting for Houses of Assembly which were earlier scheduled to hold today have been shifted. The main opposition party has also shifted primary elections for other positions. -Advertisement- Meanwhile, the PDP is yet to announce the new date for the commencement of the primaries. An official of the party who spoke with The Guardian disclosed that a meeting was fixed for 9:00 pm on Friday to decide the new dates.